notesStmt.note: Title from heading of first report (f. 1v).

msContents.summary: A collection of declarations and correspondence attributed to the Fatimid Caliph al-Ḥākim bi-Amr Allāh.

msItem.title: Nuskhat al-sijill alladhī wujida muʻallaqan ʻalá al-mashāhid fī ghaybat Mawlānā al-Imām al-Ḥākim ... .
نسخة السجل الذي وجد معلقاً على المشاهد في غيبة مولانا الامام الحاكم

author.persName: Ḥākim bi-Amr Allāh, Caliph of Egypt, 985-approximately 1021

msItem.title: Nuskhat al-sijill alladhī wujida muʻallaqan ʻalá al-mashāhid fī ghaybat Mawlānā al-Imām al-Ḥākim ... .

supportDesc.extent: 122 leaves : 205 x 150 (155 x 105) mm, bound to 205 x 150 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation added in pencil, upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left.

layoutDesc.layout: 14-15 long lines; border-ruled; one poem is set in two columns.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Naskh in black ink; pointed, fully vocalized. Headers in thuluth.

decoDesc.decoNote: Textblock border-ruled in red. Rubrications in red and green. Headers in red or yellow ink often on cloudbands with yellow, green, and black fill; some headers have more elaborate illumination in yellow and red (f. 18r, for example). Red roundels punctuate the text.

binding.p: Brown leather with blind stamped central medallion and blind tooled frame. Marbled paper pastedowns.

origin.p: Copy is undated, though perhaps copied in the 16th century. There is a note written across the spine lining with the date 864 A.H. (1460), though that date may be unrelated to this copy.
